<br>
The Sword of Truth series is a blatant ripoff of the Wheel of Time storyline.  The similarities go so far beyond coincidence its sickening.<br>
<br>
I've read every book in the Wheel of Time and every book in the Sword of Truth series.<br>
<br>
But, really though.. Sabrosia, you need to pick up book 1 of WoT and make yourself finish reading it.  The story really is quite good all the way up to book 6 - it begins to seriously drag, but if you've got the time, the later books are still worth picking up (at least in paperback).  I would say the basic storyline of the Wheel of Time is still may favorite (Rand and the Dragon Reborn.. there are still parts that give me goosebumps) but unfortunately these are getting drowned out by all the absolute worthless fluff.<br>
<br>
I have nothing against Goodkind, btw.. and I also strongly dislike Jordan now for the shit he's pulling with WoT.. but Goodkind does very very blatantly rip off themes and ideas from Jordan. To the point where I put the book I was reading down and laughed out loud at it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kullgendphlith>Kullgen dPhlith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.comcast.net/~subacca/spin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NOT A MAN<br>Dying tickles</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/04 2:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2347.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grrrrr Robert Jordan Series</span><hr size=1> Sword of Truth is Wheel of Time done <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>right. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
