I did like Chung Kuo, by David Wingrove though.  A kind of Hung Mao sci-fi take on Romance of the Three Kingdoms... kind of like Dune (which also took a startling nose dive in subsequent books).  Unfortunately, the U.S. distributor stopped distributing them after like the fourth or fifth book.<br>
