I haven't read the Sparhawk books, but I will admit that the first pentad of the Belgarion books (A.K.A.  The Belgariad) is excellent.  The second pentad (A.K.A. The Mallorean) is bound crap.  It is a complete and total rip off of the Belgariad and cheapened the original series by exploiting its popularity.  The final two books about Polgara and Belgarath are okay because they give some relatively historical information about the fantasy world, but in my opinion were simply another way to milk the series for all it was worth.  Fortunately, David and Leigh wised up and decided not to produce anymore works set in that world or we would have a nightmare akin to what Anne McCaffrey has managed to do with her Pern books.  <br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong...I love both Eddings' and McCaffrey's writings, but at some point authors need to realize that continuing a popular series no longer enriches the story...instead it makes it feel hollow and meaningless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sabrosia>Sabrosia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady of the Wolf</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/04 5:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2347.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grrrrr Robert Jordan Series</span><hr size=1> I liked the 2nd series tho...  I had a lot of fun with them...<br>
