<br>
I agree that the man himself is a bit of an arrogant dick -- if you've read his website you can see that easily enough.. but I am completely in love with his novels. His book Harpy Thyme was the first fantasy book I ever read after borrowing it by mistake.. and since then I've bought and devoured every single one of his other novels from used book stores and flea markets. He's also responsible for getting me hooked on fantasy, and in turn EQ<br>
<br>
I guess some of the elements are similar from book to book, but I enjoy the cleverness and the puns regardless. I haven't read another author who compares in that aspect.<br>
<br>
I guess another reason why I like him so much is because I've picked up the books while travelling in different places, and when I read each one over it reminds me of hitch-hiking in BC, or being stuck in a crowded bus terminal on a 6-hour layover, or starving in some other remote town trying to thumb a ride. The best times of my life! *chuckle*  <p><TABLE cellpadding="3" cellspacing="3">
